                                            <author>
                            <name>Steven Proctor</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/StevenProctor</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;Yeah, I remember you walking by us, and some others, with something like that at the Code Retreat after this past SCNA, and I think even the one after SCNA a year ago.  That is what made me think of this with the Brian&#039;s Brain.  Where it is now not the grid dimensions, but the states that are changing, along with the rules for the transition between the states.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was thinking that this would help to show how to remove the primitive obsession around the boolean of dead and alive, as it…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;Yeah, I remember you walking by us, and some others, with something like that at the Code Retreat after this past SCNA, and I think even the one after SCNA a year ago.  That is what made me think of this with the Brian&#039;s Brain.  Where it is now not the grid dimensions, but the states that are changing, along with the rules for the transition between the states.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was thinking that this would help to show how to remove the primitive obsession around the boolean of dead and alive, as it gets tricky to show three states with a single boolean.  But if you had a CellState base type for AliveState and DeadState, it would likely be straight forward to introduce a third. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;--Proctor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;cite&gt;corey haines said:&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote cite=&quot;http://coderetreat.org/forum/topics/idea-for-a-session-constraint-oh-did-i-say-conway-s-game-of-life?groupUrl=facilitators&amp;amp;#6456126Comment4478&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;xg_user_generated&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hi, Stephen,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Glad to hear you got a chance to facilitate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I often will stop the group with 5 minutes to spare and tell them that I made a mistake, it is actually a 3d grid, bounded on one side. I&#039;ll then ask them to spend the 5 minutes discussing their design and how much it would cost to change to the new requirement. I emphasize that it isn&#039;t about supporting both, but rather moving to the new, better understood requirements. It is a great thing to do if you happen to see that a lot of teams are letting the topology leak through their system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great insight!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;                        </content>
                    
